      public void setMetaPrefix​(java.lang.String metaPackage)

      Parameters:
      metaPackage - the Java package name for a Metamodel.

    • addElement

      public <T> void addElement​(PureCollection<T> collection, java.lang.Object element)
      Inserts an Object element into any typed PureCollection. Casts the Object to an element of the correct type T, before adding it to the PureCollection (either a PureList, or PureSet).
      Type Parameters:
      T - the element type parameter.
      Parameters:
      collection - the PureCollection.
      element - the element to insert.
      Throws:
      SemanticError - if the element cannot be cast to the type T.

    • createValue

      public java.lang.Object createValue​(int typeCode, java.lang.String valueText) throws SemanticError
      Factory method to create a simple value of the given type.
      Parameters:
      typeCode - the token code indicating what type of value.
      valueText - the String representation of the value.
      Returns:
      the boxed type conversion of this value.
      Throws:
      SemanticError - if the value text cannot be converted into a simple value of the type indicated by the type code.

    • setProperty

      public void setProperty​(java.lang.Object object, java.lang.String property, java.lang.Object value)
      Directly sets the named property of a model node to the given value. By reflection, accesses the Java Field declared for the Class of the node, using this to set the node's field value directly. The value must be an Object of a suitable type to be assigned.
      Parameters:
      object - the model node.
      property - the property name.
      value - the the property value.
      Throws:
      SemanticError - if there is no corresponding Java field for the property, or if the value is of an incompatible type.
